# README

## DEFAULT USER

The default user is `akamas`, which is listed as a sudoer. You can use the `sudo` command, as well as promoting to superuser with `sudo su -`.

## OPERATING SYSTEM

The underlying system is Ubuntu. You can install any missing packages with the command `sudo apt install <packagename>`.

## PERSISTENT STORAGE

The `/work` directory mounts a dedicated volume that persists across restarts. You can store Akamas artifacts, scripts, templates, and other important files there.

## SSH ACCESS

You can connect to this toolbox via ssh protocol. The only user enabled for ssh connection is 'akamas'. The password is '#PASSWORD#'.
